The paper focuses on improving mobile browser speed through client-only solutions, which is a topic related to web technologies and human-computer interaction. Therefore, cs.WEB and cs.HC are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves data analysis and machine learning techniques to understand user behavior and predict resource loading, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.IR and cs.DC. Finally, the paper discusses the design and implementation of a new browser called Tempo, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
